  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "12. by—The oldest manuscripts read, \"IN the Lord Jesus.\" So the Greek, 1Th 4:1, implying the sphere wherein such conduct is appropriate and consistent. \"We exhort you thus, as ministers IN Christ, exhorting our people IN Christ.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with quietness—quiet industry; laying aside restless, bustling, intermeddling officiousness (2Th 3:11).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "their own—bread earned by themselves, not another's bread (2Th 3:8).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
